-- Kenya Passes Legislation to Control Prices on Food, Fuel, Nation Reports
-- Eric Ombok
-- 2010-06-24T05:20:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/kenya-passes-legislation-to-control-prices-on-food-fuel-nation-reports.html

          
          
             Kenyan lawmakers yesterday passed a
legislation that allows the government to control prices of
essential commodities including food and fuel,  Daily Nation 
reported, citing parliamentary proceedings.  
 The Price Controls (Essential Goods) Bill, 2009 will not
become a law until it receives presidential approval, Nairobi-
based newspaper reported.  
